03/23/2023,748.2151(e) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,06/02/2023,06/06/2023,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium,Yes,"A child in care was administered an OTC, over the counter, antibiotic cream after an injury. The operation did not have any notation and/or medical documentation on when the antibiotic cream was administered or how often. ","As per the operation's Healthcare Manager, a standing list of PRNs can be found on the back of the MAR. Each child has a standing PRN list that identifies the correct dosage and frequency of administration based on medications guidelines. Children over the age of 12 and/or exceeding the recommended weight for Children PRN medications are placed on an Adult PRN list. If any of the standing PRN medications or supplements outside of the standing PRN list are administered, then those medications will be documented in the PRN Medication administered this period section found on the back of the MAR. This section requires the staff member administering non-prescription medications or supplements to input the date, time of administration, name of medication, dose given, staff members initials and the reason for the administration. A Response to the medication will need to be provided stating the child reaction to the medication. When a nonprescription or supplement medication is given on a daily basis, this medication is included at the front of the MAR, and it is signed out by the staff member administering the medication.
Attached is a copy of the back of the MAR that includes the information mentioned above. (Provided) The plan is to meet with our direct contact at the Pharmacy on Tuesday, June 6, 2023, to review updated MARs that include the standing PRNs listed on the front of the MAR."
