10/05/2021,748.2259(a) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,11/19/2021,11/08/2021,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium High,Yes,"During the course of this investigation, seven of seven medication records were found to be incomplete, illustrating lack of information and/or documentation.","The operation has established a new system for how they will be handling medication administration record errors in documentation and/or other corrections. As of 9/27/2021, the healthcare team at the operation will maintain custodianship of each medication administration record needing correction, with a list of staff members who need to complete said corrections. Direct care staff members and their supervisors will be sent an email with details explaining details about the medication administration records needing their attention. Direct care staff will be expected to complete these corrections within two days of receiving the email. Reminder emails will be sent to staff and their supervisors if healthcare staff notice delinquency on corrections. This will continue until medication administration records are completed in full. 

Additionally, as of 10/1/2021, all medication count sheets will include a medication rationales page with details explaining the reason the medication has been prescribed, the date the medication was started, and potential side effects to look out for as well as contraindications to the medication(s).

Medication administration records will be reviewed monthly by the healthcare staff for needed revisions, corrections, or other attention to ensure all medication is being administered and documented correctly by direct care staff. Once medication administration records have been deemed complete and ready to file by the healthcare team, they will be given to the client records manager, an individual who does not administer medications, for a second and final review to ensure all medication is being administered and documented correctly by healthcare and direct care staff."
